{
  "Id": "58a490b1-eb8a-4102-906a-f74a79c0ad1c"/*MeshFacesPoints*/,
  "Description": "\n\nCreate points at the center, corners or edges of the mesh's faces.\n\nThe size of each of the faces defines the size of the points and FX1 as the W attribute gets the radius. \n\nIn center mode uses the \"Inscribed Circle Center\".\n\nUseful combinations [LoadObj] and [DrawPoints] and more.\n\nSimilar Operators:\nTo create a point at each vertex of the connected mesh [MeshVerticesToPoints] can be used.\nTo get evenly distributed points on a mesh [PointsOnMesh] can be used.",
  "SymbolTags": "8",
  "InputUis": [
    {
      "InputId": "0a8bbf07-d77e-46e5-8598-d49e0c21735c"/*Stretch*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 892.57996,
        "Y": 2197.6238
      }
    },
    {
      "InputId": "67b24f6d-61d1-49df-9e86-4555474f91b4"/*OffsetByTBN*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1032.58,
        "Y": 2372.6238
      },
      "GroupTitle": "Additional Effects",
      "Description": "Moves the points along one of the axes of the normal"
    },
    {
      "InputId": "71d65094-f6a6-4ea7-8e3a-c0c95db5cff0"/*OffsetScale*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1172.58,
        "Y": 2652.6238
      },
      "Description": "This can be useful to \"inset\" edge loops.\n"
    },
    {
      "InputId": "803dc471-081f-48c8-b1b5-f5b5e4673518"/*Texture*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1172.58,
        "Y": 2031.0386
      }
    },
    {
      "InputId": "8365a78f-4b04-477a-b762-bcdf9e62163f"/*Mode*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 752.5799,
        "Y": 2039.2845
      },
      "Description": "Defines the output mode. This directly effects the resulting point count,  e.g. Loop mode results in FaceCount × 5 points because of an added separator. \n\nCorners is because identical to [MeshVerticesToPoints]."
    },
    {
      "InputId": "9361aeff-d96f-400c-8837-7d98fb6da99e"/*Fx1*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1172.58,
        "Y": 2302.6238
      },
      "GroupTitle": "Set Attributes",
      "Description": "Scales the W / size of the points."
    },
    {
      "InputId": "b01260c2-9766-44b2-9754-6f4a8b8dc4e3"/*Orientation*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1172.58,
        "Y": 2729.025
      },
      "Description": "UseUpVector will look more consistent in most scenarios.\nTBN (Tangent, BiTagent and Normal) will be more precise a expecially for instanciating more content at the points."
    },
    {
      "InputId": "bad1db42-201c-4d3b-8e62-82e812a8388f"/*InputMesh*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 372.6872,
        "Y": 1709.1115
      },
      "Description": "Mesh input via [LoadObj] for example"
    },
    {
      "InputId": "d5288530-4e29-4a6d-9175-7e43e2880f1d"/*ScaleWithFaceArea*/,
      "Position": {
        "X": 1032.58,
        "Y": 2617.6238
      }
    },
    {
